s. The intent was to bolster morale and thereby help soldiers survive the war. The Dumbells&#x2019; popularity was not limited to troop shows along the trenches. The group also managed a run in London&#x2019;s West End and became the first ever Canadian production to score a hit on Broadway. Touring Canada for some twelve years after the war, the Dumbells became a household name and made more than twenty-five audio recordings. If nationhood was won on the crest of Vimy Ridge, it was the Dumbells who provided the country with its earliest soundtrack. Pioneers of sketch comedy, the Dumbells are as important to the history of Canadian theatre as they are to the cultural history of early-twentieth-century Canada.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDumbells (Musical group);Revues -- 20th century -- History and criticism.;World War, 1914-1918 -- Music and the war.;Popular music -- Canada -- 1911-1920.;Popular music -- Canada -- 1921-1930. 0aPopular musiczCanaday1911-1920. 0aPopular musiczCanaday1921-1930. 0aRevuesy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xMusic and the war. 4aCultural Studies. 4aHistory: Canadian History. 4aHistory: Military History. 4aPerforming Arts. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War I.2bisacsh  aCanadian soldiers.  aCanadians in first world war.  aCanadians in world war I.  adrag show.  adumbells.  aentertain the troops.  amilitary music.  amilitary skits.  asoldier musicians.  atheatre in First World War.  atheatre in World War I.  awartime entertainment.  awartime musicians.  awartime skits.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012z978311127413308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012z978311127716540uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458882440uhttps://www